The paper deals with a computer vision problem of transferring facial makeup from a reference image to an input image in real-time. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves the use of facial feature points landmarking, which falls under the category of graphics (cs.GR). The use of illumination transfer is a technique used in multimedia (cs.MM) and computer graphics (cs.GR). The paper also mentions the efficiency of the proposed method, which could be related to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
